(168, '2021-02-25', '2021-02-25', 'On Muhammad Ali Becoming The World Heavy Weight Boxing Champion Of The World.', 'In 1964, Cassius Clay Jr, who will later be known be known as Muhammad Ali, became the world\'s Heavyweight Boxing Champion of the World. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n That was after the 22-year old underdog knocked out undisputed champion Sonny Liston at the seventh round of their title fight held in Miami Beach. Starting to box at 12 years old, he won the international Golden Gloves heavyweight title at the age of 17; and the 1960 Olympic Games light heavyweight gold in Rome. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Two days after surprising the world with his triumph, he announced that he\'d join Islam changed his name to Muhammad Ali. He\'d become the 20th century\'s greatest sporting figures.', 'May sports produce more champions and celebrities who have something worthwhile for their advocacy. May Filipinos produce more world champion boxers and athletes.', 'Everyone who competes in the games goes into strict training. They do it to get a crown that will not last, but we do it to get a crown that will last forever. 26 Therefore I do not run like someone running aimlessly; I do not fight like a boxer beating the air. 27 No, I strike a blow to my body and make it my slave so that after I have preached to others, I myself will not be disqualified for the prize. <br/>\r\n- <b> 1 Corinthians 9:25-27 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3qK8yMc', 0, NULL, 'While literal sports is challenging, its spiritual implications are more vital.'),
(169, '2021-02-25', '2021-02-25', 'On Philippines Having Two Opposing Presidents At The Same Time.', 'In 1986, the Philippines have two opposing presidents at the same times. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Corazon Aquino was proclaimed president at the Club Filipino in San Juan, Metro Manila by virtue of the Philippine Revolution. She was sworn in by Supreme Court Senior Justice Claudio Teehankee to lead the provisional government. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Ferdinand Marcos was sworn in as president an hour later inside Malacañang. He took his oath under the 1973 Constitution by Chief Justice Roman Aquino. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It was a terrible situation that would have taken much time and cost countless lives. But by the end of that day, Pres. Marcos and his family hastily left Malacañang on board US choppers. Pleaded by US President Ronald Reagan to quit, they eventually flew to Hawaii.', 'May our elections, especially the presidential always turn out fair, just and efficient, with the real winners being proclaimed swiftly.', 'He changes times and seasons; he deposes kings and raises up others. He gives wisdom to the wise and knowledge to the discerning. <br/>\r\n–<b> Daniel 2:21 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/39aBKGk', 1, NULL, 'Amidst the terrors and turmoil of the society and the bloody mess that dirty politics cause from time to time, it is reassuring that God remains sovereign.'),
(170, '2021-02-26', '2021-02-26', 'On Arrival Of First Batch Of South Korean Troops In Saigon.', 'In 1965, the first batch of South Korean troops arrived in Saigon, Vietnam to help the South Vietnamese against the communist North. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was a part of Free World Military forces, soldiers from nations allied to the USA and South Vietnam which was being attacked by communists then. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This allied group was an effort by US Pres. Lyndon Johnson who hoped to build an international consensus support of the American policies in Vietnam. The South Koreans sent a total of 47, 800 soldiers there by the end of 1969. They began to withdraw in February, 1972.', 'May Vietnam continue to develop economically, politically and spiritually. May it cease from persecuting its Christian citizens and missionaries. May Korea continue to progress on all fronts and be rewarded for its readiness to help other countries.', '16 And do not forget to do good and to share with others, for with such sacrifices God is pleased. <br/>\r\n- <b> Hebrews 13:16 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3qK8yMc', 0, NULL, 'That Korea is a much smaller nation than the US, and still helped the Americans on its plan, is a good challenge for each of us to continue assisting each other.'),
(171, '2021-02-26', '2021-02-26', 'On Apolinario Mabini Taking Oath Of Allegiance To The U.S. Before The American Collector Of Customs.', 'In 1903, Apolinario Mabini   took oath of allegiance to the United States before the American Collector of Customs. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Before that, Mabini was the main Constitutional adviser to the Filipino Revolutionary Government and the first Prime Minister of the Philippines with the creation of the Malolos Republic. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He\'s captured by the Americans in December, 1899. When he refused to swear allegiance to the US government even with incentive offers, he was deported to Guam. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n After two years of homesickness and weakening body and wanting to go back to his motherland, he finally succumbed to pressure and swore allegiance to the US government, an American condition for allowing his return.', 'May we remember and emulate Mabini\'s heroism and nationalism. May Filipino Overseas Workers overcome the temptation of homesickness and other problems. May they bring honor to their motherland wherever they may be.', 'He changes times and seasons; he deposes kings and raises up others. He gives wisdom to the wise and knowledge to the discerning. <br/>\r\n–<b> Daniel 2:21 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/368XEYA', 1, NULL, 'Amidst the terrors and turmoils of the society and the bloody mess that dirty politics cause from time to time, it is reassuring that God remains sovereign.');









(180, '2021-03-03', '2021-03-03', 'On The Birth Of Alexander Graham Bell, The Inventor Of The Telephone', 'In 1847, Alexander Graham Bell, the inventor of the telephone, was born in Edinburg, Scotland.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was awarded the first US patent for the telephone in 1876 at 29 years old. Prior to that, he was a professor of Visual Physiology in Boston. He also founded the American Telephone and Telegraph Company in 1885. Later in life, he had groundbreaking work in optical telecommunications, hydrofoils and aeronautics.', 'May more inventions be accomplished by our scientists that will be of great service to humanity. May communication be enhanced further to enable us to contact our loved ones more frequently and comprehensively.', 'and call on me in the day of trouble; I will deliver you, and you will honor me <br/>\r\n- <b>Psalm 50:15 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3bEuEtC', 0, NULL, 'Do you know that while he invented the telephone, Bell considered it an intrusion and disruption to his work that he disallowed it in his office? Do you also know that telephone may be compared to prayer? Only much better because by praying, we get in touch with God and have the chance to be blessed by Him.<br><br> We must strive to communicate with God as frequent as we can to be blessed by Him more.'),
(181, '2021-03-03', '2021-03-03', 'On The Death Of Gen. Flaviano Yengko, One Of The Youngest Filipino Generals During The Philippine-spanish War', 'In 1897, Gen. Flaviano Yengko, one of the youngest Filipino generals during the Philippine-Spanish War, died from a bullet wound in his abdomen. He was working as a clerk in the Court of First Instance at Binondo, Manila, when the Philippine Revolution began in 1896.<br><br> He fought many battles since then and was promoted very quickly by Gen. Emilio Aguinaldo. Tasked to defend the Salitran, Dasmarinas, Cavite, against the Spaniards, he was hit and died at just 22 years old.', 'May the Armed Forces of the Philippines and the Philippine National Police continue to produce real gallant, intelligent and nationalistic uniformed personnel and officers.<br><br>May lesser known heroes like Gen. Yengko be honored and emulated by the younger generation.', 'Join with me in suffering, like a good soldier of Christ Jesus.4 No one serving as a soldier gets entangled in civilian affairs, but rather tries to please his commanding officer.<br>\r\n- <b>2 Timothy 2:3-4</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2ZQcHTh', 1, NULL, 'General or just plain soldiers, every man in uniform needs to focus on prioritizing to please their commander in Chief. As Christian soldiers, we need to do the same to our Lord Jesus. We must  strive to endure hardships and please God as our Commander-in-Chief.'),
(182, '2021-03-04', '2021-03-04', 'On John Lennon Boasting That The Beatles Were More Famous Than Jesus Christ', 'In 1966, John Lennon boasted to Maureen Cleave of London\'s Evening Standard that the Beatles were more famous than Jesus Christ.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The leader of the foursome Beatles said, \"Christianity will go. It will vanish or shrink. We\'re more popular than Jesus now.\" This caused outrage among the religious. Still, church ministers in England where the Beatles came from admitted low worship service attendance while the Beatles\' concerts overflowed.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n But in the US, hate campaign against the Beatles was worse, with many gathering together to burn their records while declaring to boycott the group. Admittedly, it contributed to the eventual semi-official end to the phenomenon as Beatlemania.', 'May celebrities and other prominent people remain humble and God-fearing. May we refrain from patroni, ing those who are proven to be proud and disrespectful to God and spiritual matters.', 'Does the ax raise itself above the person who swings it, or the saw boast against the one who uses it? As if a rod were to wield the person who lifts it up, or a club brandish the one who is not wood<br/>\r\n- <b>Isaiah 10:15 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2NFp4iJ', 0, NULL, 'The Bible has so many warnings and guidelines in relation to pride and boasting. We must  strive to remain humble and instead boast about God\'s greatness.'),
(183, '2021-03-04', '2021-03-04', 'On The Ratification Of Separate Extradition Treaties Between Rp & UK, India & Spain', 'In 2014, the Senate concurred the ratification of separate extradition treaties between the Philippines and the governments of the United Kingdom, India and Spain. International extradition is the act where one nation delivers a person accused  or con, icted of committing a crime in another country, over to their law enforcement.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n These treaties are considered to be a very effective mechanism in obtaining the return of international fugitives in order for them to face the consequences of their criminal actions.</i><br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Senator Mirriam Santiago, who proposed this, said, \"Corrupt politicians and their partners-in-crime have a tendency to flee to other countries to escape the long arm of justice. We are making sure that arm is longer and stronger. They should have nowhere to hide .\".', 'May the Philippines forge such treaty with other countries as well, And may these treaties be fulfilled by all parties concerned.', 'Whoever conceals their sins does not prosper, but the one who confesses and renounces them finds mercy.<br>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 28:13</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', ' https://bit.ly/2ZP95RI', 1, NULL, 'This reminds us about our sins – we can not escape from them, especially if we are not willing to repent. We must strive to admit our sins to God and not hide them.');




(188, '2021-03-07', '2021-03-07', 'On Sheikh Mujib Rahman Becoming The First Democratic Leader Of Bangladesh', 'In 1973, Sheikh Mujib Rahman became the first democratic leader of Bangladesh. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after the head of the Bangladesh Independence Movement won a landslide victory in the country\'s first general elections.<br><br>Once a British colony and part of Pakistan, Bangladesh declared independence in March, 1971.  Through the help of India, Bangladesh gained independence and released Sheikh Mujib from prison to become Bangladesh Prime Minister. His people confirmed his rule in a democratic elections, compelling Pakistan to recognize the independence of Bangladesh', 'May Bangladesh continue to develop as a democratic country.<br><br>May other countries, like India (in this case), continue to help other nations attain their independence.May all of US be wiser in electing our leaders.', 'Therefore, as God\'s chosen people, holy and dearly loved, clothe yourselves with compassion, kindness, humility, gentleness and patience<br/>\r\n- <b>Colossians 3:12</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/0lIjkEG', 0, NULL, 'Do you know that God Himself has opted to elect Christians? This is for a heavenly call and cause. We must strive to value our calling from God and serve Him well.'),
(189, '2021-03-07', '2021-03-07', 'On The Beginning Of Direct Trade With Spain, In 1820, direct trade with Spain began.', 'Prior to that, trading was mainly through merchant ships known as the Manila Galleons journeying from Manila to Mexico and vice versa.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The Spanish government granted shipping subsidies, dramatically increasing foreign trade and causing economic progress for the Philippines', 'May our trade relations with other countries develop and help steer our economy to progress. May pour economic leaders protect the plight of our local businessmen and farmers against the harmful effects of globalization. <br><br>May our traders be truly nationalistic and honest.',  'The LORD detests dishonest scales,  but accurate weights find favor with him.<br>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 11:1</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/vlIlw75', 1, NULL, 'It\'s good to note that God\'s salvation comes to anyone regardless of their race and background. We must strive to refrain from being discriminatory of others just because they do not belong to our group; but instead, strive to do God\'s will.'),
(190, '2021-03-08', '2021-03-08', 'On The Official Celebration Of The International Women\'s Day', 'In 1975, the United Nations started to officially celebrate the International Women\'s Day. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was their fitting project for the holding of 1975 as the International Women\'s Year.<br><br> It was also a tribute to the many women in Russia, Germany, Austria, Denmark and the United States who have unified in different periods between 1909 to 1917 in order to protest against their countries\' low salary, 12-hour daily working job and to demand  for their right to vote.', 'May women in the Philippines and the world over be given more space for exercising their women\'s rights, and contributing to their particular society', 'I also want the women to dress modestly, with decency and propriety, adorning themselves, not with elaborate hairstyles or gold or pearls or expensive clothes, 10 but with good deeds, appropriate for women who profess to worship God<br/>\r\n- <b>1 Timothy 2:9-10</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/AlITiP2', 0, NULL, ' The Bible mentions notable heroines like Deborah, Ruth, Esther, Lydia, Priscilla and the Blessed Mary. They contributed immensely to the progress of their people and the furtherance of God\'s kingdom. Thank God indeed for women!<br><br>Still, the Bible has clear instructions to women regardless of their race, especially if they are Christians. We must recognize women who are modest and implement modesty ourselves.'),
(191, '2021-03-08', '2021-03-08', 'On The Birth Of Gregorio Zara, A National Scientist Awardee In 1978', 'In 1902,  Gregorio Zara, inventor of 30 devices and equipment, and a National Scientist Awardee in 1978, was born in Lipa City, Batangas. A Master\'s degree holder in Aeronautical Engineering from the University of Michigan in the US, and a Doctorate degree achiever in Physics from Sorbone University in Paris, he invented the first video phone in 1955.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Among his other inventions are alcohol-fueled airplane engine, solar water heater, sun stove, solar battery, propeller cutting machine, and  microscope with collapsible stage. He died in 1978 at 76 and was accorded a state funeral at the Libingan ng mga Bayani', 'May the Philippines produce more brilliant scientists and inventors who would make more useful devices and equipment.',  '6 By the word of the LORD the heavens were made, their starry host by the breath of his mouth.8 Let all the earth fear the LORD; let all the people of the world revere him.  9 For he spoke, and it came to be; he commanded, and it stood firm  .<br>\r\n- <b>Psalm 33:6, 8-9</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/hlIT9n2', 1, NULL, 'While we should admire scientists who invent useful things from some raw materials, we should respect God even more because He creates from nothing, only through His word.We must strive to  recognize God as the greatest inventor and serve Him.');








(196, '2021-03-11', '2021-03-11', 'On Lithuania Proclaiming Its Independence From The USSR', 'In 1940, the Russian occupied it, only to be replaced by the Germans in 1941. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1941, the pro-soviet communist regime was installed there. In the late 1980s, Russian leader Mikhail Gorbachev initiated his policy of Glasnost (openness), encouraging the Lithuanians to proclaim independence', 'May Lithuania continue to develop and have cordial relations with the Russians. May smaller countries being manipulated by more powerful ones find freedom and independence.', 'Live as free people, but do not use your freedom as a cover-up for evil; live as God\"s slaves. 17 Show proper respect to everyone, love the family of believers, fear God, honor the emperor.<br/>\r\n- <b>1 Peter 2:16-17</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', ' https://cutt.ly/LlI0UsJ', 0, NULL, 'Every individual and nation craves freedom and independence. Sometimes, the problem is not being free but living out that freedom effectively. We strive to live according to the freedom that God gives us in honor of Him and for the edification of others.'),
(197, '2021-03-11', '2021-03-11', 'On Japanese Lieutenant Hiroo Onoda Surrendering To Pres. Ferdinand Marcos', 'In 1974, Japanese Liutenant Hiroo Onoda formally surrendered to Pres Marcos, ending 29-year of hiding in Mindoro after World War II. He lived in the jungles and mountains of Lubang Island along with the three other soldiers, who believed that the war has not ended yet, and did not surrender in August 1945 along with the rest of the Japanese imperial army.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n By 1972, he was left alone with two soldiers being killed by the police and the other one surrendering in 1949. He surrendered only when his commanding officer, Major Yoshimi Taniguchi returned to the Philippines to bring him back to Japan.', 'May Japanese people contributed to develop respect and admiration for the Filipinos and the Philippines; and vice versa. May those who need to surrender, especially the criminals on the loose, finally come to the fold of the law.',  'For whoever wants to save their life will lose it, but whoever loses their life for me and for the gospel will save it.<br>\r\n- <b>Mark 8:35</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/XlI09Mg', 1, NULL, 'While we can hide from others for a long time, no one can escape the presence and rule of God. We must strive to recognize that God knows us totally and sees us everywhere we may be.'),
(198, '2021-03-12', '2021-03-12', 'On Mahatma Gandhi, Beginning A Civil Disobedience Campaign', 'In 1930, Mahatma Gandhi began another civil disobedience campaign in protest of the British monopoly of salt in their country. The leader of the India Nationalist Movement set out on a 388 km-march to the coastal town of Dandi on the Arabian Sea from Sabarmati to make salt from seawater. <br><br> Britain\'s Salt Act then prohibited Indians from collecting or selling the latter\'s staple in diet. Indians were forced to buy salt from the British. Gandhi had only 78 followers when they began the march. Along the way, he addressed the public. By the time they reached the seaside, he had a crowd of tens of thousands', 'May India continue to develop as a free nation. May it maintain cordial relations with its former colonizers – Britain. May salt production and refining continue the world over.', 'You are the salt of the earth. But if the salt loses its saltiness, how can it be made salty again? It is no longer good for anything, except to be thrown out and trampled underfoot.<br/>\r\n- <b>Matthew 5:13</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/YlFCSkk', 0, NULL, 'While salt may be considered insignificant by many, it\'s vital in many ways for making food tastier and preserving fresh meat and others. No wonder the Lord Jesus compared salt to Christians. We must strive to manifest the quality of salt – adding tastiness and freshness to our society.'),
(199, '2021-03-12', '2021-03-12', 'On Supreme Court Creating The Philippine Judicial Academy (PHILJA)', 'In 1996, The Philippine Judicial Academy (PHILJA) was created by the Supreme Court. This was in accordance with Republic Act No. 8557 as a \"training school for justices, judges, court personnel, lawyers and aspirants to judicial posts.\"<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It\"s the academy\'s mission to provide and implement a curriculum for judicial education, and conduct seminars, workshops and other training programs that upgrade them. It\"s main academy is located in Tagaytay City and is being overseen by eight qualified justices and judges comprising the Governing Board headed by Chief Justice of the Supreme Court', 'May the Philippine Supreme Court remain independent from outside interference.<br><br>May its personnel remain loyal to their country, people, constitution and God more than to any personality.',  'Learn to do right; seek justice. Defend the oppressed. Take up the cause of the fatherless; plead the case of the widow.<br>\r\n- <b>Isaiah 1:17</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/vlFC9xx', 1, NULL, 'While educational training for our justices and their peers are always useful, their fundamental responsibility emanates from God Himself and remains the same.<br><br>We must strive to defend the poor, marginalized and abused.');





(200, '2021-03-13', '2021-03-13', 'On US Army Launching The K-9', 'In 1942, the US Army launched K-9. This is the training of certain dogs which is also called the \"War Dog Program\". <br><br> In this program, dogs are taught to carry messages along the complex network of teachers and to provide some measures of psychological comfort to the soldiers.', 'May the programs of the governments in using certain dogs in special beneficial purposes succeed, without jeopardizing the health of these concerned animals. May we all be truly caring for our dogs and other pets.', 'As a dog returns to its vomit, so a fool repeats his folly.<br/>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 26:11</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/wlG4POz', 0, NULL, 'While dogs are man\'s best friends and are capable of doing many useful things for us, they also reflect one of man\'s bad characteristics – which is foolishness. We must strive to avoid returning to our vomit.'),
(201, '2021-03-13', '2021-03-13', 'On Dr. Leon Ma. Guerrero Discovering \"Walis-walis\" To Replace Tea', 'In 1943, Dr. Leon Ma. Guerrero, the first Filipino industrial scientist, discovered \"Walis-walis\" to replace tea. Also called the \"Father of Philippine Pharmacy\", this forensic chemist eventually authored a study on \"Medical Plants\"" on 174 types of plants in the country with healing elements, including \"walis-walis\"', 'May more Filipino scientists and chemists discover more indigenous materials and products that will advance health and healing.<br><br> May our government assists fully our scientists in their researches and projects.', 'Fruit trees of all kinds will grow on both banks of the river. Their leaves will not wither, nor will their fruit fail. Every month they will bear fruit, because the water from the sanctuary flows to them. Their fruit will serve for food and their leaves for healing.<br>\r\n- <b>Ezekiel 47:12</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/ElG7F6E', 1, NULL, 'Do you know that it\'s actually God\'s intention and design to give medicinal values to certain plants? He reiterated it to the prophet Ezekiel in a vision of the coming New Jerusalem.<br><br>We must strive to appreciate God for giving medicinal values to plants and to use them ourselves.'),
(202, '2021-03-14', '2021-03-14', 'On The Birth Of Albert Einstein, The Greatest Scientist Of All Times.', 'In 1879, Albert Einstein, considered the greatest scientist of all times, was born in Germany. This German-American physicist and 1921 Nobel Laureate is best known for his Theory of Relativity.<br><br>It led to the use of atom as power source. He\'s been honored as the man of the millennium and the number one genius of the world primarily for that.', 'May more scientists and genius of all kinds rise up from among the ranks of Filipinos and other nationalities. May they truly be helpful to the community.', 'As a dog returns to its vomit, so a fool repeats his folly.<br/>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 26:11</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/4lHiFyH', 0, NULL, 'While we appreciate people with high IQs, we must remember God\'s definition of one who is truly wise.<br><br>We must strive to be truly wise according to God\'s standards.'),
(203, '2021-03-14', '2021-03-14', 'On The Establishment Of The Manila Electric Company (MERALCO)', 'In 1903, the Manila Electric Company (Meralco), which supplies electric power to Metro Manila residents at present, was established. Originally named, Manila electric Railroad and Light Company, it was the first power company given franchise to operate electric cars, called Travania and provide electricity in Manila and surrounding areas.', 'May the technology of making, storing and disseminating electricity throughout the country advance and be more economical.<br><br>May we all learn to conserve electricity.',  'But you will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes on you; and you will be my witnesses in Jerusalem, and in all Judea and Samaria, and to the ends of the earth<br>\r\n- <b>Acts 1:8</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/JlHoP01', 1, NULL, 'While we appreciate electric power, we must understand the Holy Spirit is greater than all powers combined. He gives us (1) freedom [2 Corinthians 3:17]; (2) love [Romans 5:5]; (3) wisdom and self-discipline [2 Timothy 1:7]; and (4) inner strength to live a victorious Christian life [Galatians 5:16-17\' Romans 8:2-12].<br><br>We must strive to appreciate the person, power and ministry of the Holy Spirit.');





(204, '2021-03-15', '2021-03-15', 'On Christopher Columbus Returning To Spain After His First Voyage To The New World', 'In 1943, Christopher Columbus returned to Spain after his first voyage to the New World. He began his expedition on August 3,1942 with three ships – Santa Maria, Pinta and Nina from Palos, dela Frontera, Spain to the Indies.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He first landed in the Bahamas, sailing on behalf of the Spanish crown in a new attempt to find a western route to Asia.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n His first of four journeys to Antilles, Venezuela and Central America took seven months.\r\n', 'May pro-God, pro-people and pro- environment exploration succeed. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n May our very own Benham Rise and other Philippine territories be protected from foreign powers that want to exploit it for their own needs.', 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, \"Depart, go up from here, you and the people whom you have brought up from the land of Egypt, to the land of which I swore to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, saying, ‘To your descendants I will give it..\"</i><br/>\r\n- <b>Exodus 33:1</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/RlHpN1M', 0, NULL, 'In the Bible, perhaps the greatest type of expedition was that ordered by God Himself to the foremost leaders of Israel, namely Abraham and Moses. This was a journey of great faith in God.'), 
(205, '2021-03-15', '2021-03-15', 'On The First Flight Of Philippine Airlines (PAL)', 'In 1941, Philippine Airlines (PAL), Asia\'s first airline, made its maiden flight. This was one month after PAL was incorporated by a group of businessmen.<br><br>This flight took off from Nielsen Airfield in Makati and landed in Baguio City, a distance of about 255 kilometers. <br><br>The twin-engine, five-seater Beech Model 18 aircraft was used.', 'May PAL and the other Filipino airlines succeed in being at par with the world\'s best in every facet, from its world class planes and service to its competitive personnel.', 'But those who wait upon the Lord will renew their strength. They will soar on wings like eagles; they will run and not grow weary; they will walk and not faint<br>\r\n- <b>Isaiah 40:31</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/alHkgQh', 1, NULL, 'People can fly in many ways and forms. The Bible, in fact, compares certain people to eagles- the strongest, highest-flying and most elegant bird of all times.<br><br>We must strive to wait on the Lord to soar like an eagle.'),
(206, '2021-03-16', '2021-03-16', 'On Robert Goddard Launching The World\'s First Liquid-Fueled Rocket', 'In 1926, the worlds\' first liquid-fueled rocket was successfully launched by American Robert Goddard. Launched at Auburn, Massachusetts, the rocket traveled for 2.5 seconds at a speed of about  97 kilometers per hour.<br><br>It was 10 feet tall, made out of thin pipes and was fueled by liquid oxygen and gasoline (The first rockets were gunpowder-propelled).<br><br> This achievement inspired the world that space travel is indeed possible and moved scientists to develop further rocket science.\r\n', 'May rocket science and technology continue to advance and develop space travel and research.', 'He spreads out the northern skies over empty space; he suspends the earth over nothing.<br/>\r\n- <b>Job 26:7</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/mlHzbtN', 0, NULL, 'Do you know that the Bible has particular verses that give us hints about space and the earth design?<br><br>We must recognize that the Bible reveals some scientifically proven statements about space, heavens and the earth.'), 
(207, '2021-03-16', '2021-03-16', 'On Ferdinand Magellan\'s Discovering The Philippines.',  'In 1521, Ferdinand Magellan discovered the Philippines. His expedition landed in Homonhon, a small island in Samar. He named the newly discovered land, Archipelago of St. Lazarus which was later changed to Islas De Pilipinas by Ruy Lopez de Villalobos in honor of Philip II.', 'May more and more foreigners discover and appreciate the beauty of our country and people.<br><br>May the Department of Tourism come up with better programs of promoting our country without sacrificing our resources, people and national integrity.', 'Oh, Lord, You have searched me and known me. 2 You know when I sit and when I rise. You perceive my thought from afar<br>\r\n- <b>Psalm 139:1-2</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/GlHz034', 1, NULL, 'It\'s good to be discovered and appreciated for who we really are. But our problem is how to keep others appreciate us after they\'ve discovered our limitations, weaknesses and failures.<br><br>God does!<br><br>We must  appreciate God for loving us supremely despite  Him knowing even our worst sins and state.');





  (208, '2021-03-17', '2021-03-17', 'On Golda Meir Becoming Israel\'s First And Only Woman Prime Minister', 'In 1969, Golda Meir became Israel\'s first and only woman Prime Minister. This was after the then 71 year-old Ukraine-born Jewish teacher was elected to the said post.<br><br>Migrating to Palestine in 1921, she came into politics as a member, then as Minister of the Labour Party and Foreign Minister of Israel.<br><br>She was called as the \"Iron Lady of Israel\" until she resigned as prime minister in 1974 for health reasons.\r\n', 'May Jewish women be given ample chances to contribute to the security and progress of Israel.<br><br>May the current prime minister of Israel as well as the future ones continue to lead their people to fulfill God' plan for them as His chosen people.', '8 Barak said to her, \"If you go with me, I will go; but if you don’t go with me, I won’t go.\" 9 \"Certainly I will go with you,\" said Deborah. \"But because of the course you are taking, the honor will not be yours, for the LORD will deliver Sisera into the hands of a woman.\" So Deborah went with Barak to Kedesh.<br/>\r\n- <b>Judges 4:8-9</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/4lHxLnH', 0, NULL, 'Long before Golda Mier, Deborah was one of the earliest national leaders of the ancient Israel. She became prominent because their then commander-in-chief and king, Barak, relied on her. Together, they overcame their more powerful enemies and led Israel to forty years of peace.<br><br>We must  strive to  give room for women to excel in their fields to help in the progress of societies and for appreciating them'), 
  (209, '2021-03-17', '2021-03-17', 'On The Death Of Ramon Magsaysay, The Seventh Pres. Of The Philippines.', 'In 1957, Ramon Magsaysay, the seventh president of the Philippines, died in a plane crash in Mt. Manungal, Cebu. An engineer-guerilla who became the Secretary of National Defense, his conquest of the Hukbalahap was Asia' first victory against communism.<br><br> His overwhelming triumph to presidency was made firmer when he led numerous pro-poor government projects and innovation. This included opening the gates of Malacañang to the common people, irrigation for farms, artesian wells everywhere, and peace and order down to the barrios.<br><br>No wonder the whole nation mourned with his sudden and tragic death', 'May we have more national leaders who will have the same passion and focus for the masses and the poor.<br><br>May fatal accidents be prevented, especially involving the key leaders of the country.', 'He who oppresses the poor shows contempt for their Maker, but whoever is kind to the needy honors God.<br>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 14:31</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/vlHcx1q', 1, NULL, 'Poor-loving-leaders do not only become more endearing to the people. They also bring more satisfaction and honor to God.<br><br>We must strive to be kind to those in need.'),
  (210, '2021-03-18', '2021-03-18', 'On Blaise Pascal\'s First Public Bus Service', 'In 1662, the first public bus service in the world began in Paris, France. This was officially launched by Blaise Pascal, who would later be known more as a brilliant mathematician, scientist and inventor.<br><b>This bus service was called \"Five-Penny Couches\", with seven horse-drawn vehicles running along regular routes. Granted a royal monopoly by then King Louis XIV, each vehicle carried eight passengers.<br><br>While it didn\'t last long because of the feudal system then, it inspired others for much better bus services later.\r\n', 'May the public bus system improve further.May the MRT, LRT and subway trains system being planned to be added in the Philippines succeed as soon as possible.', ' \"But you, Daniel, roll up and seal the words of the scroll until the time of the end. Many will go here and there to increase knowledge.\"<br/>\r\n- <b>Daniel 12:4</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/ElHcKXR', 0, NULL, 'Do you know that the advancement in science and technology leading to fast transport systems in land, sea and air is somewhat prophesied in the Bible?<br><br>We must strive to appreciate and utilize well all the advancement in science, technology and intrastructures.'), 
  (211, '2021-03-18', '2021-03-18', 'On The Birth Of Fidel Ramos, Eight President Of The Third Republic.', 'In 1928, Fidel Ramos, eight president of the third Republic, was born in Lingayen, Pangasinan. A scholar of the US Military Academy in West Point, he was a Vietnam War veteran who was instrumental in the successful EDSA People Power Revolution of 1986.<br><br>Though he' a relative of the then president Ferdinand Marcos, General Ramos stood in his conviction for the Filipinos and opposed the former. AsiaWeek magazine called him \"a Filipino peacemaker and stabilizer\". He helped the Aquino administration to overcome numerous coup attempts.<br><br>His own presidency in 1992 was marked by relative peace and progress', 'May more leaders have greater conviction for the people and peace that go beyond kingship and political alliance.', '\" Blessed are the peacemakers, for they will be called sons of God.\".<br>\r\n- <b>Matthew 5:9</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/XlHn5wj', 1, NULL, 'After all, it is honorable and God-exalting to be peacemakers.<br><br>We must strive to manifest and promote peace among our people.');




(212, '2021-03-19', '2021-03-19', 'On The First Telecast Of The Oscars Academy Awards', 'In 1953, the world\'s most prestigious movie honors – the Oscars Academy Awards was telecast for the first time on NBC. The National Broadcasting Company TV network showed the 25th yearly awards ceremony live from the RKO Pantages Theatre in Hollywood with Bob Hope as the master of ceremonies.<br><br>Organized in 1927 with its maiden awarding in 1929, the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences is dedicated to advance the film industry.<br><br>The Awards recognizes excellence in cinematic achievement with the voters being their own members at the Academy.\r\n', 'May the film industry support also socially relevant and spiritually uplifting movies and actors, not just purely entertaining and controversial ones.<br><br>May Christian producers, actors and technical people succeed in penetrating the movie industry.', '9 So we make it our goal to please God, whether we are at home in the body or away from it. 10 For we must all appear before the judgment seat of Christ, so that each of us may receive what is due us for the things done while in the body, whether good or bad<br/>\r\n- <b>2 Corinthians 5:9-10</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', ' https://cutt.ly/ElHm0m1', 0, NULL, 'If the Oscars gives awards to those who excel in their film and acting crafts, God Himself will give awards to those who serve Him well. This is called the Bema Judgment.<br><br>We must strive to please and honor God in our lives to ensure that He will reward us come judgment day.'), 
(213, '2021-03-19', '2021-03-19', 'On The Birth Of Gabriela Silang.', 'In 1731, Gabriela SIlang was born in Barangay Caniogan, Santa, Ilocos Sur. Although widowed at a young age, she showed extreme courage and love for our country that she continued to lead the battle for our freedom waged by her assassinated husband Diego.<br><br>The first woman to have led a revolt in the Philippines, this white-horse-riding heroine was executed by the Spaniards when she' just 32 years old.<br><br>Today' most active women' group in the country is named after her', 'May our women epitomize her and the likes of Deborah who also led her Jewish countrymen in beating the Canaanites (Judges 3 & 4).', 'So may all your enemies perish, LORD! But may all who love you be like the sun when it rises in its strength.<br>\r\n- <b>Judges 5:31 </b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/hlHQFFz', 1, NULL, 'In Deborah\'s case, her strength lies in her faith and worship of God who delivers.  Notice below hear declaration and prayer in a song she sang after beating their enemies.<br><br>We must strive to be praiseful to God even in the midst of our life' battles.'),
(214, '2021-03-20', '2021-03-20', 'On The Establishment Of The Republican Party', 'In 1854, the Republican Party, one of only two political parties in the United States, was established. This was after the opponents of the expansion of slavery in the US territories met in Ripon, Wisconsin, and decided to formally unite to battle the issue.<br><br>They adhered to classical liberalism, advocating civil liberties under the rule of law, and encouraging economic freedom.<br><br>Abraham Lincoln, the first Republican to become the US President, eventually  banned slavery in their country in 1865.\r\n', 'May the Republicans continue to espouse civil liberty an economic freedom without infringing on the religious rights of Christians.<br><br>May the two-party system of the US flourish, and may the Philippine government consider having the same party system since the multiparty and personality-based politics among the Filipinos seem not really beneficial to the Filipino.', ' 3 For rulers hold no terror for those who do right, but for those who do wrong. Do you want to be free from fear of the one in authority? Then do what is right and you will be commended. 4 For the one in authority is God\'s servant for your good. But if you do wrong, be afraid, for rulers do not bear the sword for no reason. They are God\'s servants, agents of wrath to bring punishment on the wrongdoer<br/>\r\n- <b>Romans 13:3-4</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/KlHWTC7', 0, NULL, 'Whatever party system there may be in a particular government, it would do well if citizens support their leaders in every way.<br><br>We must strive to elect the most qualified leaders and submit to them.'), 
(215, '2021-03-20', '2021-03-20', 'On The Establishment Of The Marilao-Malolos Bulacan Defense Lines Against The Americans.', 'In 1899, Gen. Emilio Aguinaldo established the Marilao-Malolos Bulacan defense lines against the Americans. This was done with 25,000 Filipino soldiers and volunteers. However, the more equipped Americans led by Col. Frederick Funston overran this defense line on March 31, with eight of their soldiers killed and 105 wounded.<br><br>The Filipinos, with unnumbered casualties, were forced to flee to Nueva Ecija.', 'May the Armed Forces of the Philippines strengthen the defense lines of its territories, especially the Philippine West Sea. May it somehow defend our fishermen being harassed by the Chinese forces there.<br><br>On a larger scale, may the Phil. Government strengthen its defense lines against anarchy, rebellion, political manipulations and terrorism.', 'Trust in him at all times, you people; pour out your hearts to him, for God is our refuge.<br>\r\n- <b>Psalm 62:8 </b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/8lHElmf ', 1, NULL, 'Of course, may we not forget that both individually and collectively, our main defender in life is God Himself.<br><br>We must strive to trust God, especially in the midst of severe trials.');





(216, '2021-03-21', '2021-03-21', 'On Martin Luther King, Jr. Beginning The March For African-American Rights In Alabama', 'In 1965, Nobel Peace Prize winner Martin Luther King, Jr., an American Baptist Minister and civil rights activist, began the march from Selma to Montgomery in Alabama. Calling for African-American voting rights, he led  3,200 civil rights demonstrators to the 84 km- three day march to the Alabama State capital.<br><br>The march was marked by riots and oppositions along the way perpetrated by the majority American whites, the Alabama State Police and even State Governor George Wallace.<br><br>Luther Jr\'s march did not only reach its destination. It also solicited global support, leading to the National Voting Rights Act later.\r\n', 'May human and civil rights be full recognized by governments the world over. May rights leaders and proponents exemplify their call, and be protected from abusive government officials and citizens who are rabid oppositions to their lobbying.', '\"1 If you see your fellow Israelite\' ox or sheep straying, do not ignore it but be sure to take it back to its owner. 2 If they do not live near you or if you do not know who owns it, take it home with you and keep it until they come looking for it. Then give it back. 3 Do the same if you find their donkey or cloak or anything else, they have lost. Do not ignore it. 4 If you see your fellow Israelite\'s donkey or ox fallen on the road, do not ignore it. Help the owner get it to its feet\".<br/>\r\n- <b>Deuteronomy 22:1-4</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/plHEMuR', 0, NULL, 'Whatever party system there may be in a particular government, it would do well if citizens support their leaders in every way.<br><br>We must strive to elect the most qualified leaders and submit to them.'), 
(217, '2021-03-21', '2021-03-21', 'On The Death Of Pura Kalaw Villanueva,The Most Famous Filipina Feminist-Journalist-Beauty Queen.', 'In 1954, Pura Villanueva Kalaw, the most famous Filipina feminist-journalist-beauty queen turned into one, died at 67 years old. An Ilonga who was also the first \"Queen of the Manila Carnival\" and \"Queen of the Orient\", she founded the Women\'s Club Suffrage Drive.<br><br>It took her and her group 31 years of relentless campaigning for women to be allowed to vote before she succeeded.<br><br>In 1937, the Philippine Assembly gave Filipino women the right to vote, initially through a plebiscite.', 'May the Philippines continue to recognize women\'s rights and give them ample space not only for self-fulfillment but also for contributing to the welfare of the country.', 'He makes my feet like the feet of a deer; He enables me to stand on the heights.<br>\r\n- <b>Psalm 18:33</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/plHRF9x', 1, NULL, 'Indeed, we can all do great things and accomplish community-uplifting tasks regardless of our sex. That is especially true if we have God Himself as our backer.<br><br>We must strive to assimilate and recognize God\'s enabling for us..'),
(218, '2021-03-22', '2021-03-22', 'On The Establishment Of The Arab League By Seven Countries', 'In 1945, the Arab League was established in Cairo, Egypt by seven countries. It was built to promote economic growth in the region, solve disagreements between its members, and coordinate political goals. The league\'s initial council was composed of the representatives from Egypt, Syria, Lebanon, Trans-Jordan, Saudi Arabia, Iraq and Yemen.<br><br>Fifteen more Arab nations joined it later and even established a common market in 1965.\r\n', 'May the Arab League members and organizations continue to grow economically, socially and culturally.<br><br>May  this league somehow finally accept the sovereignty of Israel and respect Christianity and Christians within its territories.', '6 For you are a people holy to the LORD your God. The LORD your God has chosen you out of all the peoples on the face of the earth to be his people, his treasured possession.7 The LORD did not set his affection on you because you were more numerous than other peoples, for you were the fewest of all peoples. 8 But it was because the LORD loved you and kept the oath he swore to your ancestors that he brought you out with a mighty hand and redeemed you from the land of slavery, from the power of Pharaoh king of Egypt.<br/>\r\n- <b>Deuteronomy 7:6-8</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/PlHR3ey', 0, NULL, 'While it\'s a well-known secret that the Arab League was also established to oppose, if not destroy Israel, It\'s good for the Jews that the God of the Bible  has a special commitment to them.<br><br>We must strive to respect Muslim countries and the Jewish  nation alike.'), 
(219, '2021-03-22', '2021-03-22', 'On The Birth Of Emilio Aguinaldo, The Philippines\' First President.', 'In 1869, Emilio Aguinaldo, the Philippines\' first president, was born in Kawit, Cavite. He became Kawits\' first municipal mayor at 26. He joined Andres Bonifacio at the Katipunan.  He became head of the KKK\'s Magdalo group and led his forces to win in Kawit, Imus and Binakayan.<br><br>He proclaimed Philippine independence against the Spaniards on June 12, 1898. He later fought the Americans but was arrested in 1901.<br><br>After the restoration of peace, he led the life of a farmer.', 'May all Filipinos reflect patriotism, especially our national leaders.<br><br>May we choose as our local and national leaders those who have risen from the ranks and have proven themselves worthy with their good track record of public service, not just because they are famous or personable.', 'And we, who with unveiled faces all reflect the Lord\'s glory, are being transformed into His likeness with ever increasing glory; which comes from the Lord, who is the Spirit.<br>\r\n- <b>2 Corinthians 3:18</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/xlHTTFP', 1, NULL, 'Still, there is a much greater reflection that we need to emit – the image of God.We must strive to reflect God\'s characteristics to others.');








(228, '2021-03-27', '2021-03-27', 'On Using Fingerprint Evidence For The First Time To Solve A British Mystery Case', 'In 1905, fingerprint evidence was used for the first time to solve a British murder case. The victims were Thomas and Ann Farrow, shopkeepers in South London who were found by their neighbors bludgeoned to death in their homes. The finger prints of the murderers, brothers Alfred and Albert Stratton, were discovered on the Farrow\'s empty cash box by Scotland yard investigators. <br><br>The brothers were convicted and hanged on May 23, 1905.\r\n', 'May the fingerprinting technique, DNA and forensic investigation technology improve and be enhanced. May only the truly guilty criminals and lawbreakers be convicted and punished.', 'He is the radiance of the glory of God and the exact imprint of his nature, and he upholds the universe by the word of his power<br/>\r\n- <b>Hebrews 1:3</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/SlHPHoG', 0, NULL, 'Do you know that the Lord Jesus Christ is in a way, a finger print of the unseen God the Father? That means God leaves his mark through Jesus’ works.<br><br>We must strive to recognize that the Lord Jesus Christ is the imprints of the unseen God.'),  
(229, '2021-03-27', '2021-03-27', 'On The Distribution Of Certificates Of Lot Allocation To 10,000 Urban Poor Families In Las Pinas City.', 'In 2001, certificates of lot allocation were distributed to 10,000 urban poor families in Las Pinas City. This was personally done by then Pres. Gloria Arroyo at the CAA High School Annex grounds for the government’s Housing Project in the said city.<br><br>According to former Congress Speaker Manuel Villar, this project took eight years and three presidents before being accomplished.  The beneficiaries were mostly squatter people who live in the area since the 1960s.<br>This project was replicated through the Housing and Urban Development Coordinating Council in many other places in Luzon, helping informal settlers have their own house, finally.', 'May the housing program of the government expand and succeed.<br><br>May the impoverished squatter people find hope and courage to take responsibility and advance in life through God\'s help.', 'Whoever shuts their ears to the cry of the poor will also cry out and not be answered.<br>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 21:13</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/1lHAnR7', 1, NULL, 'At the same time, may we all have practical sympathy for the poor.  After all, God Himself cares for our welfare. <br><br>We must strive to help the poor and the needy in our society.'),
(230, '2021-03-28', '2021-03-28', 'On The Salvation Army Being Recognized In The U.S', 'In 1885, the Salvation Army was officially recognized in the United States. Founded in London, England in 1865 by Methodist preacher William Booth and his wife Catherine, SA is a Protestant Church and an international charitable institution.<br><br>It sent delegates to the US on this day and was warmly received by Pres. Grover Cleveland, who immediately gave them his personal endorsement to begin ministering in America.<br><br>Today, SA reports a worldwide membership of over 1.7 million in 131 countries, with special mission to bring the gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ to the poor by meeting their spiritual and physical needs.\r\n', 'May the Salvation Army and other Christian para-church organizations (groups which work hand-in-hand with the local churches) flourish in the Philippines and elsewhere.', 'The Spirit of the Lord is on me, because He has anointed me  to proclaim good news to the poor. He has sent me to proclaim freedom for the prisoners  and recovery of sight for the blind, to set the oppressed free, 19 to proclaim the year of the Lord\'s favor<br/>\r\n- <b>Luke 4:18-19</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/FlHA1nj', 0, NULL, 'In fairness to the SA, they are striving to imitate spiritual and social ministry of the Lord Jesus Christ.<br><br>We must strive to provide practical help to others, especially  the needy and marginalized.'),   
(231, '2021-03-28', '2021-03-28', 'On Pres. Ferdinand Marcos Signing The Dairy Industry Development Act.', 'In 1979, Pres. Ferdinand Marcos signed into law the Dairy Industry Development Act. This was to hasten the production, processing, marketing and distribution of local milk products.<br><br>Later, it led to the signing of the National Dairy Development Act of 1995 and the creation of the National Dairy Authority and the National Nutrition Council.<br><br>That\'s why in 1995, the National Nutrition Month was launched with the theme: \“For Strong Bones and Teeth, Drink Milk\”. It emphasized the importance of milk in everyone\'s diet.', 'May the dairy industry in the country develop some more, with the Filipinos able to raise sufficient number of healthy cows throughout the year. And not rely so much on imported milk.<br><br>May Filipino mothers practice breastfeeding their babies and succeed on this for healthier generation of kids.', 'Like newborn babies, crave pure spiritual milk, so that by it you may grow up in your salvation.<br>\r\n- <b>1 Peter 2:2</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/KlHSNXj', 1, NULL, 'Do you know that the Bible is compared to milk for its nutritious effects?<br><br>We must strive to meditate the Bible to grow in our faith.');





(232, '2021-03-29', '2021-03-29', 'On The Withdrawal Of The US Troops From Vietnam', 'In 1973, US troops withdrew from Vietnam, eventually ending direct American involvement in the Vietnam War after eight years. This was two months after the Vietnam peace agreement was signed by representatives from the US. North and South Vietnam in Paris, France.<br><br>The pact included the holding of ceasefire throughout Vietnam, the American troops leaving, North Vietnam freeing the remaining US prisoners of war, and the unification of north and south through peaceful means.<br><br>Costing the lives of 58,000 American lives, and as many as two million Vietnamese, the Vietnam War was the most unpopular and longest foreign war in US history.\r\n', 'May Vietnam continue to be united and progress more in all aspects.<br><br>May the Vietnamese and the Americans develop their relationship.<br><br>May the Vietnamese government desist from persecuting Christians.', 'You will hear of wars and rumors of wars, but see to it that you are not alarmed. Such things must happen, but the end is still to come. 7 Nation will rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom. All these are the beginning of birth pains<br/>\r\n- <b>Matthew 24:6-8</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/ClHDbp5', 0, NULL, 'While we all want wars between nations to stop, these will continue in a general sense because the Lord Jesus prophesied it.<br><br>We must strive to be optimistic even in times of war and other global and national disorders and chaos.'),   
(233, '2021-03-29', '2021-03-29', 'On The Founding Of New People\'s Army Of The Communist Party Of The Philippines.', 'In 1969, the New People\'s Army of the Communist Party of the Philippines was founded. This was through the merging of Bernabe Buscayno\'s Huk\'s peasant army and CPP founder Jose Maria Sison\'s revolutionary group.<br><br>The NPA operates armed guerrilla activities in the rural areas, particularly in inaccessible places.  They also collect revolutionary taxes from companies in communities where they operate.', 'May the source of NPA\'s rebellion which include poverty, social inequality and injustice be adequately solved by the government.<br><br>May God\'s perfect will be done about the aborted peace talks between the Philippine government and the Communist Party of the Philippines.', 'Let everyone be subject to the governing authorities, for there is no authority except that which God has established. The authorities that exist have been established by God.2 Consequently, whoever rebels against the authority is rebelling against what God has instituted, and those who do so will bring judgment on themselves.<br>\r\n- <b>Romans 13:1-2</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', ' https://cutt.ly/qlHFyDT ', 1, NULL, 'While some may justify rebellion against the government, we must recognize that God does not approve it.<br><br>We must strive to support and submit to our government.'),
(234, '2021-03-30', '2021-03-30', 'On US Pres. Ronald Reagan Surviving An Assassination Attempt', 'In 1981, US Pres. Ronald Reagan was shot and survived an assassination attempt. The then 70-year old president was shot six times by a deranged John Hinckley, Jr. with a small 22-caliber pistol as he was walking out of a Washington hotel.<br><br>One bullet passed inches away from his heart and was rushed to Washington Hospital, where it was removed from his lungs after two hours of surgery.<br><br>On April 11, he returned to the White House to formally resume his presidential office works.\r\n', 'May our leaders be protected from assassination attempts and other evil plots. May they finish their respective terms of office successfully.<br><br>Blessing and enabling to all presidential security groups and its equivalence throughout the world.', '\“Cursed is anyone who kills their neighbor secretly.\” Then all the people shall say, \“Amen!\” 25 \“Cursed is anyone who accepts a bribe to kill an innocent person.\” Then all the people shall say, \“Amen!\”  <br/>\r\n- <b>Deuteronomy 27:24-25</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/dlHGVod', 0, NULL, 'While we do not desire that our national leaders be assassinated, we must strongly desist from literally or even symbolically being involved in the killing of our countrymen.<br><br>We must strive to resist any temptation even in our minds to have others killed.'),  
(235, '2021-03-30', '2021-03-30', 'On US Gen. Elwell Otis Establishing The Department Of Instruction For The Philippines.', 'In 1900, US Gen. Elwell Otis officially established the Department of Instruction for the Philippines. He placed Captain Albert Todd of the Sixth Artillery in charge of the said department.<br><br>Prior to that, the education in the Philippines under the Spaniards was \“strictly sectarian, ungraded, with no prescribed course of study and no definite standards for each year\”.<br><br>With the founding of the DI, non-sectarian and free graded public schools were built and trained teachers from the US deployed.', 'May the educational system in the country continue to develop on all fronts to ensure free quality education that trains globally competitive citizens.<br><br>Blessings and enabling to the staff and personnel of the Department of Education (DepEd) , the Commission on Higher Education (CHE), and the Technical Education and Skills Development Authority (TESDA).', 'Start children off on the way they should go, and even when they are old they will not turn from it.<br>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 22:6</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/xlHHmZQ', 1, NULL, 'Even the Bible teaches us about the importance of early education and continuing learning.<br><br>We must strive to educate properly the younger generation as well as ourselves.');







(236, '2021-03-31', '2021-03-31', 'On The Opening And Dedication Of Eiffel Tower In France', 'In 1889, the Eiffel Tower in Paris, France was formally opened and dedicated. This was presided over by Gustave Eiffel, its designer and graced by Pierre Tirard, French Prime Minister and other dignitaries.<br><br>Eiffel\'s design was the winner of the French government’s international competition in honor of the centenary of the French Revolution.<br><br>Standing at 984 feet and consisting of an iron framework supported on four masonry piers, it has three platforms with observation deck on each. It remains one of the most famous tourist spots in the world.\r\n', 'May the Eiffel Tower continue to be protected and enhanced by the government authorities.<br><br>May its staff continue to welcome tourists effectively.', 'Suppose one of you wants to build a tower. Won\'t you first sit down and estimate the cost to see if you have enough money to complete it? 29 For if you lay the foundation and are not able to finish it, everyone who sees it will ridicule you, 30 saying, \‘This person began to build and wasn\'t able to finish\'.<br/>\r\n- <b>Luke 14:28-30</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/VlHHBiS', 0, NULL, 'Building towers take time owing to its complicated designs and height; as well as the actual tedious process of building it.<br><br>In the Bible, one major principle is taught in building towers that relate directly to life.<br><br>We must strive to plan and pray intensely before actually undertaking hat we want to accomplish.'),
(231, '2021-03-31', '2021-03-31', 'On The First Roman Catholic Mass In The Philippines.', 'In 1521, the first Roman Catholic Mass in the Philippines was held in an island called Masao (Limasawa to most historians). This was upon the order of Ferdinand Magellan and under Father Pedro de Valderrama’s officiating. Datus Kolambu and Siaiu were the first natives present then. Magellan set up a cross on the island and took possession of the archipelago for Spain, which he named Islands of St. Lazarus. It marked the beginning of the Roman Catholic religion in the Philippines.', 'May the Roman Catholic church and the rest of so-called Christian groups be more faithful to the Lord Jesus Christ and God’s written Word.<br><br>May Filipino Christians be effective missionaries to the other nations and races.', 'Blessed is the nation whose God is the LORD, the people he chose for his inheritance.<br>\r\n- <b>Psalm 33:12</b>', '<i>\"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories\"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://cutt.ly/6lHJiYF', 1, NULL, 'Symbolically, Magellan\'s chosen name for the Philippines was appropriate to a certain extent. Lazarus was a close friend of the Lord Jesus Christ whom he raised from the dead.<br><br>The Filipinos in general are relatively cognizant of the Lord Jesus Christ, and have somewhat risen from the pantheism and animism that hounded our ancestors, to serve God.<br><br>We must strive to God-fearing citizens of our own country.');
